{
  "stem": "14900.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I was telling you about this Polish German girl and the SS man who came to visit her home.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, a week or so later-- as I said, we were not permitted to have meat, poultry, eggs, milk, many things except very limited rations.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And because I didn't look very Jewish-- I had long, reddish brown hair in pigtails-- we decided I would not wear the Jewish star.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All Jews had to wear this star from day of occupation, within a week or so.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Didn't have a chance to tell you that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Also had to walk in the middle of the road, were not permitted on sidewalks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They were used for all kinds of menial labor, cleaning up the horse manure in the street, cleaning out latrines, being kicked and beaten.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The older, the worse the treatment.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The more religious, the worse the treatment was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't mean that their belief was that much stronger, but the more obviously Jewish they looked, according to the German stereotype, the worse it got for them.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I did not wear the star, one, for my own protection, so I wouldn't get beaten, have to walk in the middle of the road.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Two, I became the chief procurer of food, of the forbidden foods for us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Let's face it, the milk came from the next door neighbor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't have that far to go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The eggs were someplace else.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Chickens came from one of the farmers who lived in short proximity.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "However, the Jewish butcher, I had to walk about eight, ten blocks past the church.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
